{"id":"eschew","term":"Eschew","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>From old French eschever, “to flee from” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 1:1\">Job 1:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:8\">8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:3\">2:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 3:11\">1 Pet. 3:11</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Job 1:1","Genesis 1:8","Genesis 2:3","1 Peter 3:11"]}